quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  10,62,"Those who are close to God shall certainly have no fear, nor shall they grieve"
  10,63,For those who believe and are mindful of God
  10,64,"there is good news in this life and in the Hereafter: the Word of God shall never change. That is the supreme triumph"
  10,65,"Do not let their words grieve you. Surely, all might and glory belongs to God alone; He is the all-hearing, the all-knowing"
  10,66,"Surely, all who are in the heavens and on the earth belong to Him. What do those follow, who appeal to associates instead of to God? They merely follow conjecture and they are only guessing"
  10,67,"It is He who has made the night dark for you so that you may rest in it, and the day a source of light. Surely, there are signs in this for a people who listen"
  10,68,"They say, \"God has begotten a son.\" Glory be to Him. He is the Self-Sufficient One; everything in the heavens and on the earth belongs to Him. Do you have any authority for this? Would you ascribe to God something which you do not know"
  10,69,"Say, \"Those who invent falsehoods about God shall not prosper"
  10,70,"Their portion is short-lived enjoyment in this world; but to Us they shall return. Then We shall make them taste a severe punishment, because of their denial of truth"